2227/// Visitor to rewrite instructions using p particular slice of an alloca
2228/// to use a new alloca.
2229///
2230/// Also implements the rewriting to vector-based accesses when the partition
2231/// passes the isVectorPromotionViable predicate. Most of the rewriting logic
2232/// lives here.
2233class llvm::sroa::AllocaSliceRewriter
2234 : public InstVisitor<AllocaSliceRewriter, bool> {
2235 // Befriend the base class so it can delegate to private visit methods.
2236 friend class InstVisitor<AllocaSliceRewriter, bool>;
2237
2238 using Base = InstVisitor<AllocaSliceRewriter, bool>;
2239
2240 const DataLayout &DL;
2241 AllocaSlices &AS;
2242 SROA &Pass;
2243 AllocaInst &OldAI, &NewAI;
2244 const uint64_t NewAllocaBeginOffset, NewAllocaEndOffset;
2245 Type *NewAllocaTy;
2246
2247 // This is a convenience and flag variable that will be null unless the new
2248 // alloca's integer operations should be widened to this integer type due to
2249 // passing isIntegerWideningViable above. If it is non-null, the desired
2250 // integer type will be stored here for easy access during rewriting.
2251 IntegerType *IntTy;
2252
2253 // If we are rewriting an alloca partition which can be written as pure
2254 // vector operations, we stash extra information here. When VecTy is
2255 // non-null, we have some strict guarantees about the rewritten alloca:
2256 // - The new alloca is exactly the size of the vector type here.
2257 // - The accesses all either map to the entire vector or to a single
2258 // element.
2259 // - The set of accessing instructions is only one of those handled above
2260 // in isVectorPromotionViable. Generally these are the same access kinds
2261 // which are promotable via mem2reg.
2262 VectorType *VecTy;
2263 Type *ElementTy;
2264 uint64_t ElementSize;
2265
2266 // The original offset of the slice currently being rewritten relative to
2267 // the original alloca.
2268 uint64_t BeginOffset = 0;
2269 uint64_t EndOffset = 0;
2270
2271 // The new offsets of the slice currently being rewritten relative to the
2272 // original alloca.
2273 uint64_t NewBeginOffset, NewEndOffset;
2274
2275 uint64_t SliceSize;
2276 bool IsSplittable = false;
2277 bool IsSplit = false;
2278 Use *OldUse = nullptr;
2279 Instruction *OldPtr = nullptr;
2280
2281 // Track post-rewrite users which are PHI nodes and Selects.
2282 SmallSetVector<PHINode *, 8> &PHIUsers;
2283 SmallSetVector<SelectInst *, 8> &SelectUsers;
2284
2285 // Utility IR builder, whose name prefix is setup for each visited use, and
2286 // the insertion point is set to point to the user.
2287 IRBuilderTy IRB;
2288
2289public:
2290 AllocaSliceRewriter(const DataLayout &DL, AllocaSlices &AS, SROA &Pass,
2291 AllocaInst &OldAI, AllocaInst &NewAI,
2292 uint64_t NewAllocaBeginOffset,
2293 uint64_t NewAllocaEndOffset, bool IsIntegerPromotable,
2294 VectorType *PromotableVecTy,
2295 SmallSetVector<PHINode *, 8> &PHIUsers,
2296 SmallSetVector<SelectInst *, 8> &SelectUsers)
2297 : DL(DL), AS(AS), Pass(Pass), OldAI(OldAI), NewAI(NewAI),
2298 NewAllocaBeginOffset(NewAllocaBeginOffset),
2299 NewAllocaEndOffset(NewAllocaEndOffset),
2300 NewAllocaTy(NewAI.getAllocatedType()),
2301 IntTy(IsIntegerPromotable
2302 ? Type::getIntNTy(
2303 NewAI.getContext(),
2304 DL.getTypeSizeInBits(NewAI.getAllocatedType()))
2305 : nullptr),
2306 VecTy(PromotableVecTy),
2307 ElementTy(VecTy ? VecTy->getElementType() : nullptr),
2308 ElementSize(VecTy ? DL.getTypeSizeInBits(ElementTy) / 8 : 0),
2309 PHIUsers(PHIUsers), SelectUsers(SelectUsers),
2310 IRB(NewAI.getContext(), ConstantFolder()) {
2311 if (VecTy) {
2312 assert((DL.getTypeSizeInBits(ElementTy) % 8) == 0 &&
2313 "Only multiple-of-8 sized vector elements are viable");
2314 ++NumVectorized;
2315 }
2316 assert((!IntTy && !VecTy) || (IntTy && !VecTy) || (!IntTy && VecTy));
2317 }
2318
2319 bool visit(AllocaSlices::const_iterator I) {
2320 bool CanSROA = true;
2321 BeginOffset = I->beginOffset();
2322 EndOffset = I->endOffset();
2323 IsSplittable = I->isSplittable();
2324 IsSplit =
2325 BeginOffset < NewAllocaBeginOffset || EndOffset > NewAllocaEndOffset;
2326 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " rewriting " << (IsSplit ? "split " : ""));
2327 LLVM_DEBUG(AS.printSlice(dbgs(), I, ""));
2328 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n");
2329
2330 // Compute the intersecting offset range.
2331 assert(BeginOffset < NewAllocaEndOffset);
2332 assert(EndOffset > NewAllocaBeginOffset);
2333 NewBeginOffset = std::max(BeginOffset, NewAllocaBeginOffset);
2334 NewEndOffset = std::min(EndOffset, NewAllocaEndOffset);
2335
2336 SliceSize = NewEndOffset - NewBeginOffset;
2337
2338 OldUse = I->getUse();
2339 OldPtr = cast<Instruction>(OldUse->get());
2340
2341 Instruction *OldUserI = cast<Instruction>(OldUse->getUser());
2342 IRB.SetInsertPoint(OldUserI);
2343 IRB.SetCurrentDebugLocation(OldUserI->getDebugLoc());
2344 IRB.SetNamePrefix(Twine(NewAI.getName()) + "." + Twine(BeginOffset) + ".");
2345
2346 CanSROA &= visit(cast<Instruction>(OldUse->getUser()));
2347 if (VecTy || IntTy)
2348 assert(CanSROA);
2349 return CanSROA;
2350 }

2353 // Make sure the other visit overloads are visible.
2354 using Base::visit;

2356 // Every instruction which can end up as a user must have a rewrite rule.
2357 bool visitInstruction(Instruction &I) {
2358 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " !!!! Cannot rewrite: " << I << "\n");
2359 llvm_unreachable("No rewrite rule for this instruction!");
2360 }

2362 Value *getNewAllocaSlicePtr(IRBuilderTy &IRB, Type *PointerTy) {
2363 // Note that the offset computation can use BeginOffset or NewBeginOffset
2364 // interchangeably for unsplit slices.
2365 assert(IsSplit || BeginOffset == NewBeginOffset);
2366 uint64_t Offset = NewBeginOffset - NewAllocaBeginOffset;
2367
2368#ifndef NDEBUG
2369 StringRef OldName = OldPtr->getName();
2370 // Skip through the last '.sroa.' component of the name.
2371 size_t LastSROAPrefix = OldName.rfind(".sroa.");
2372 if (LastSROAPrefix != StringRef::npos) {
2373 OldName = OldName.substr(LastSROAPrefix + strlen(".sroa."));
2374 // Look for an SROA slice index.
2375 size_t IndexEnd = OldName.find_first_not_of("0123456789");
2376 if (IndexEnd != StringRef::npos && OldName[IndexEnd] == '.') {
2377 // Strip the index and look for the offset.
2378 OldName = OldName.substr(IndexEnd + 1);
2379 size_t OffsetEnd = OldName.find_first_not_of("0123456789");
2380 if (OffsetEnd != StringRef::npos && OldName[OffsetEnd] == '.')
2381 // Strip the offset.
2382 OldName = OldName.substr(OffsetEnd + 1);
2383 }
2384 }
2385 // Strip any SROA suffixes as well.
2386 OldName = OldName.substr(0, OldName.find(".sroa_"));
2387#endif
2388
2389 return getAdjustedPtr(IRB, DL, &NewAI,
2390 APInt(DL.getIndexTypeSizeInBits(PointerTy), Offset),
2391 PointerTy,
2392#ifndef NDEBUG
2393 Twine(OldName) + "."
2394#else
2395 Twine()
2396#endif
2397 );
2398 }

2400 /// Compute suitable alignment to access this slice of the *new*
2401 /// alloca.
2402 ///
2403 /// You can optionally pass a type to this routine and if that type's ABI
2404 /// alignment is itself suitable, this will return zero.
2405 unsigned getSliceAlign(Type *Ty = nullptr) {
2406 unsigned NewAIAlign = NewAI.getAlignment();
2407 if (!NewAIAlign)
2408 NewAIAlign = DL.getABITypeAlignment(NewAI.getAllocatedType());
2409 unsigned Align =
2410 MinAlign(NewAIAlign, NewBeginOffset - NewAllocaBeginOffset);
2411 return (Ty && Align == DL.getABITypeAlignment(Ty)) ? 0 : Align;
2412 }

2414 unsigned getIndex(uint64_t Offset) {
2415 assert(VecTy && "Can only call getIndex when rewriting a vector");
2416 uint64_t RelOffset = Offset - NewAllocaBeginOffset;
2417 assert(RelOffset / ElementSize < UINT32_MAX && "Index out of bounds");
2418 uint32_t Index = RelOffset / ElementSize;
2419 assert(Index * ElementSize == RelOffset);
2420 return Index;

2428
2429 Value *rewriteVectorizedLoadInst() {
2430 unsigned BeginIndex = getIndex(NewBeginOffset);
2431 unsigned EndIndex = getIndex(NewEndOffset);
2432 assert(EndIndex > BeginIndex && "Empty vector!");
2433
2434 Value *V = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(NewAI.getAllocatedType(), &NewAI,
2435 NewAI.getAlignment(), "load");
2436 return extractVector(IRB, V, BeginIndex, EndIndex, "vec");
2437 }
2438
2439 Value *rewriteIntegerLoad(LoadInst &LI) {
2440 assert(IntTy && "We cannot insert an integer to the alloca");
2441 assert(!LI.isVolatile());
2442 Value *V = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(NewAI.getAllocatedType(), &NewAI,
2443 NewAI.getAlignment(), "load");
2444 V = convertValue(DL, IRB, V, IntTy);
2445 assert(NewBeginOffset >= NewAllocaBeginOffset && "Out of bounds offset");
2446 uint64_t Offset = NewBeginOffset - NewAllocaBeginOffset;
2447 if (Offset > 0 || NewEndOffset < NewAllocaEndOffset) {
2448 IntegerType *ExtractTy = Type::getIntNTy(LI.getContext(), SliceSize * 8);
2449 V = extractInteger(DL, IRB, V, ExtractTy, Offset, "extract");
2450 }
2451 // It is possible that the extracted type is not the load type. This
2452 // happens if there is a load past the end of the alloca, and as
2453 // a consequence the slice is narrower but still a candidate for integer
2454 // lowering. To handle this case, we just zero extend the extracted
2455 // integer.
2456 assert(cast<IntegerType>(LI.getType())->getBitWidth() >= SliceSize * 8 &&
2457 "Can only handle an extract for an overly wide load");
2458 if (cast<IntegerType>(LI.getType())->getBitWidth() > SliceSize * 8)
2459 V = IRB.CreateZExt(V, LI.getType());
2460 return V;
2461 }
2462
2463 bool visitLoadInst(LoadInst &LI) {
2464 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " original: " << LI << "\n");
2465 Value *OldOp = LI.getOperand(0);
2466 assert(OldOp == OldPtr);
2467
2468 AAMDNodes AATags;
2469 LI.getAAMetadata(AATags);
2470
2471 unsigned AS = LI.getPointerAddressSpace();
2472
2473 Type *TargetTy = IsSplit ? Type::getIntNTy(LI.getContext(), SliceSize * 8)
2474 : LI.getType();
2475 const bool IsLoadPastEnd = DL.getTypeStoreSize(TargetTy) > SliceSize;
2476 bool IsPtrAdjusted = false;
2477 Value *V;
2478 if (VecTy) {
2479 V = rewriteVectorizedLoadInst();
2480 } else if (IntTy && LI.getType()->isIntegerTy()) {
2481 V = rewriteIntegerLoad(LI);
2482 } else if (NewBeginOffset == NewAllocaBeginOffset &&
2483 NewEndOffset == NewAllocaEndOffset &&
2484 (canConvertValue(DL, NewAllocaTy, TargetTy) ||
2485 (IsLoadPastEnd && NewAllocaTy->isIntegerTy() &&
2486 TargetTy->isIntegerTy()))) {
2487 LoadInst *NewLI = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(NewAI.getAllocatedType(), &NewAI,
2488 NewAI.getAlignment(),
2489 LI.isVolatile(), LI.getName());
2490 if (AATags)
2491 NewLI->setAAMetadata(AATags);
2492 if (LI.isVolatile())
2493 NewLI->setAtomic(LI.getOrdering(), LI.getSyncScopeID());
2494
2495 // Any !nonnull metadata or !range metadata on the old load is also valid
2496 // on the new load. This is even true in some cases even when the loads
2497 // are different types, for example by mapping !nonnull metadata to
2498 // !range metadata by modeling the null pointer constant converted to the
2499 // integer type.
2500 // FIXME: Add support for range metadata here. Currently the utilities
2501 // for this don't propagate range metadata in trivial cases from one
2502 // integer load to another, don't handle non-addrspace-0 null pointers
2503 // correctly, and don't have any support for mapping ranges as the
2504 // integer type becomes winder or narrower.
2505 if (MDNode *N = LI.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_nonnull))
2506 copyNonnullMetadata(LI, N, *NewLI);
2507
2508 // Try to preserve nonnull metadata
2509 V = NewLI;
2510
2511 // If this is an integer load past the end of the slice (which means the
2512 // bytes outside the slice are undef or this load is dead) just forcibly
2513 // fix the integer size with correct handling of endianness.
2514 if (auto *AITy = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(NewAllocaTy))
2515 if (auto *TITy = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(TargetTy))
2516 if (AITy->getBitWidth() < TITy->getBitWidth()) {
2517 V = IRB.CreateZExt(V, TITy, "load.ext");
2518 if (DL.isBigEndian())
2519 V = IRB.CreateShl(V, TITy->getBitWidth() - AITy->getBitWidth(),
2520 "endian_shift");
2521 }
2522 } else {
2523 Type *LTy = TargetTy->getPointerTo(AS);
2524 LoadInst *NewLI = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(
2525 TargetTy, getNewAllocaSlicePtr(IRB, LTy), getSliceAlign(TargetTy),
2526 LI.isVolatile(), LI.getName());
2527 if (AATags)
2528 NewLI->setAAMetadata(AATags);
2529 if (LI.isVolatile())
2530 NewLI->setAtomic(LI.getOrdering(), LI.getSyncScopeID());
2531
2532 V = NewLI;
2533 IsPtrAdjusted = true;
2534 }
2535 V = convertValue(DL, IRB, V, TargetTy);
2536
2537 if (IsSplit) {
2538 assert(!LI.isVolatile());
2539 assert(LI.getType()->isIntegerTy() &&
2540 "Only integer type loads and stores are split");
2541 assert(SliceSize < DL.getTypeStoreSize(LI.getType()) &&
2542 "Split load isn't smaller than original load");
2543 assert(DL.typeSizeEqualsStoreSize(LI.getType()) &&
2544 "Non-byte-multiple bit width");
2545 // Move the insertion point just past the load so that we can refer to it.
2546 IRB.SetInsertPoint(&*std::next(BasicBlock::iterator(&LI)));
2547 // Create a placeholder value with the same type as LI to use as the
2548 // basis for the new value. This allows us to replace the uses of LI with
2549 // the computed value, and then replace the placeholder with LI, leaving
2550 // LI only used for this computation.
2551 Value *Placeholder = new LoadInst(
2552 LI.getType(), UndefValue::get(LI.getType()->getPointerTo(AS)));
2553 V = insertInteger(DL, IRB, Placeholder, V, NewBeginOffset - BeginOffset,
2554 "insert");
2555 LI.replaceAllUsesWith(V);
2556 Placeholder->replaceAllUsesWith(&LI);
2557 Placeholder->deleteValue();
2558 } else {
2559 LI.replaceAllUsesWith(V);
2560 }
2561
2562 Pass.DeadInsts.insert(&LI);
2563 deleteIfTriviallyDead(OldOp);
2564 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to: " << *V << "\n");
2565 return !LI.isVolatile() && !IsPtrAdjusted;
2566 }
2567
2568 bool rewriteVectorizedStoreInst(Value *V, StoreInst &SI, Value *OldOp,
2569 AAMDNodes AATags) {
2570 if (V->getType() != VecTy) {
2571 unsigned BeginIndex = getIndex(NewBeginOffset);
2572 unsigned EndIndex = getIndex(NewEndOffset);
2573 assert(EndIndex > BeginIndex && "Empty vector!");
2574 unsigned NumElements = EndIndex - BeginIndex;
2575 assert(NumElements <= VecTy->getNumElements() && "Too many elements!");
2576 Type *SliceTy = (NumElements == 1)
2577 ? ElementTy
2578 : VectorType::get(ElementTy, NumElements);
2579 if (V->getType() != SliceTy)
2580 V = convertValue(DL, IRB, V, SliceTy);
2581
2582 // Mix in the existing elements.
2583 Value *Old = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(NewAI.getAllocatedType(), &NewAI,
2584 NewAI.getAlignment(), "load");
2585 V = insertVector(IRB, Old, V, BeginIndex, "vec");
2586 }
2587 StoreInst *Store = IRB.CreateAlignedStore(V, &NewAI, NewAI.getAlignment());
2588 if (AATags)
2589 Store->setAAMetadata(AATags);
2590 Pass.DeadInsts.insert(&SI);
2591
2592 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to: " << *Store << "\n");
2593 return true;
2594 }
2595
2596 bool rewriteIntegerStore(Value *V, StoreInst &SI, AAMDNodes AATags) {
2597 assert(IntTy && "We cannot extract an integer from the alloca");
2598 assert(!SI.isVolatile());
2599 if (DL.getTypeSizeInBits(V->getType()) != IntTy->getBitWidth()) {
2600 Value *Old = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(NewAI.getAllocatedType(), &NewAI,
2601 NewAI.getAlignment(), "oldload");
2602 Old = convertValue(DL, IRB, Old, IntTy);
2603 assert(BeginOffset >= NewAllocaBeginOffset && "Out of bounds offset");
2604 uint64_t Offset = BeginOffset - NewAllocaBeginOffset;
2605 V = insertInteger(DL, IRB, Old, SI.getValueOperand(), Offset, "insert");
2606 }
2607 V = convertValue(DL, IRB, V, NewAllocaTy);
2608 StoreInst *Store = IRB.CreateAlignedStore(V, &NewAI, NewAI.getAlignment());
2609 Store->copyMetadata(SI, {LLVMContext::MD_mem_parallel_loop_access,
2610 LLVMContext::MD_access_group});
2611 if (AATags)
2612 Store->setAAMetadata(AATags);
2613 Pass.DeadInsts.insert(&SI);
2614 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to: " << *Store << "\n");
2615 return true;
2616 }
2617
2618 bool visitStoreInst(StoreInst &SI) {
2619 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " original: " << SI << "\n");
2620 Value *OldOp = SI.getOperand(1);
2621 assert(OldOp == OldPtr);
2622
2623 AAMDNodes AATags;
2624 SI.getAAMetadata(AATags);
2625
2626 Value *V = SI.getValueOperand();
2627
2628 // Strip all inbounds GEPs and pointer casts to try to dig out any root
2629 // alloca that should be re-examined after promoting this alloca.
2630 if (V->getType()->isPointerTy())
2631 if (AllocaInst *AI = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(V->stripInBoundsOffsets()))
2632 Pass.PostPromotionWorklist.insert(AI);
2633
2634 if (SliceSize < DL.getTypeStoreSize(V->getType())) {
2635 assert(!SI.isVolatile());
2636 assert(V->getType()->isIntegerTy() &&
2637 "Only integer type loads and stores are split");
2638 assert(DL.typeSizeEqualsStoreSize(V->getType()) &&
2639 "Non-byte-multiple bit width");
2640 IntegerType *NarrowTy = Type::getIntNTy(SI.getContext(), SliceSize * 8);
2641 V = extractInteger(DL, IRB, V, NarrowTy, NewBeginOffset - BeginOffset,
2642 "extract");
2643 }
2644
2645 if (VecTy)
2646 return rewriteVectorizedStoreInst(V, SI, OldOp, AATags);
2647 if (IntTy && V->getType()->isIntegerTy())
2648 return rewriteIntegerStore(V, SI, AATags);
2649
2650 const bool IsStorePastEnd = DL.getTypeStoreSize(V->getType()) > SliceSize;
2651 StoreInst *NewSI;
2652 if (NewBeginOffset == NewAllocaBeginOffset &&
2653 NewEndOffset == NewAllocaEndOffset &&
2654 (canConvertValue(DL, V->getType(), NewAllocaTy) ||
2655 (IsStorePastEnd && NewAllocaTy->isIntegerTy() &&
2656 V->getType()->isIntegerTy()))) {
2657 // If this is an integer store past the end of slice (and thus the bytes
2658 // past that point are irrelevant or this is unreachable), truncate the
2659 // value prior to storing.
2660 if (auto *VITy = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(V->getType()))
2661 if (auto *AITy = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(NewAllocaTy))
2662 if (VITy->getBitWidth() > AITy->getBitWidth()) {
2663 if (DL.isBigEndian())
2664 V = IRB.CreateLShr(V, VITy->getBitWidth() - AITy->getBitWidth(),
2665 "endian_shift");
2666 V = IRB.CreateTrunc(V, AITy, "load.trunc");
2667 }
2668
2669 V = convertValue(DL, IRB, V, NewAllocaTy);
2670 NewSI = IRB.CreateAlignedStore(V, &NewAI, NewAI.getAlignment(),
2671 SI.isVolatile());
2672 } else {
2673 unsigned AS = SI.getPointerAddressSpace();
2674 Value *NewPtr = getNewAllocaSlicePtr(IRB, V->getType()->getPointerTo(AS));
2675 NewSI = IRB.CreateAlignedStore(V, NewPtr, getSliceAlign(V->getType()),
2676 SI.isVolatile());
2677 }
2678 NewSI->copyMetadata(SI, {LLVMContext::MD_mem_parallel_loop_access,
2679 LLVMContext::MD_access_group});
2680 if (AATags)
2681 NewSI->setAAMetadata(AATags);
2682 if (SI.isVolatile())
2683 NewSI->setAtomic(SI.getOrdering(), SI.getSyncScopeID());
2684 Pass.DeadInsts.insert(&SI);
2685 deleteIfTriviallyDead(OldOp);
2686
2687 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to: " << *NewSI << "\n");
2688 return NewSI->getPointerOperand() == &NewAI && !SI.isVolatile();
2689 }

2691 /// Compute an integer value from splatting an i8 across the given
2692 /// number of bytes.
2693 ///
2694 /// Note that this routine assumes an i8 is a byte. If that isn't true, don't
2695 /// call this routine.
2696 /// FIXME: Heed the advice above.
2697 ///
2698 /// \param V The i8 value to splat.
2699 /// \param Size The number of bytes in the output (assuming i8 is one byte)
2700 Value *getIntegerSplat(Value *V, unsigned Size) {
2701 assert(Size > 0 && "Expected a positive number of bytes.");
2702 IntegerType *VTy = cast<IntegerType>(V->getType());
2703 assert(VTy->getBitWidth() == 8 && "Expected an i8 value for the byte");
2704 if (Size == 1)
2705 return V;
2706
2707 Type *SplatIntTy = Type::getIntNTy(VTy->getContext(), Size * 8);
2708 V = IRB.CreateMul(
2709 IRB.CreateZExt(V, SplatIntTy, "zext"),
2710 ConstantExpr::getUDiv(
2711 Constant::getAllOnesValue(SplatIntTy),
2712 ConstantExpr::getZExt(Constant::getAllOnesValue(V->getType()),
2713 SplatIntTy)),
2714 "isplat");
2715 return V;
2716 }
2717
2718 /// Compute a vector splat for a given element value.
2719 Value *getVectorSplat(Value *V, unsigned NumElements) {
2720 V = IRB.CreateVectorSplat(NumElements, V, "vsplat");
2721 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " splat: " << *V << "\n");
2722 return V;
2723 }
2724
2725 bool visitMemSetInst(MemSetInst &II) {
2726 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " original: " << II << "\n");
2727 assert(II.getRawDest() == OldPtr);
2728
2729 AAMDNodes AATags;
2730 II.getAAMetadata(AATags);
2731
2732 // If the memset has a variable size, it cannot be split, just adjust the
2733 // pointer to the new alloca.
2734 if (!isa<Constant>(II.getLength())) {
2735 assert(!IsSplit);
2736 assert(NewBeginOffset == BeginOffset);
2737 II.setDest(getNewAllocaSlicePtr(IRB, OldPtr->getType()));
2738 II.setDestAlignment(getSliceAlign());
2739
2740 deleteIfTriviallyDead(OldPtr);
2741 return false;
2742 }
2743
2744 // Record this instruction for deletion.
2745 Pass.DeadInsts.insert(&II);
2746
2747 Type *AllocaTy = NewAI.getAllocatedType();
2748 Type *ScalarTy = AllocaTy->getScalarType();
2749
2750 const bool CanContinue = [&]() {
2751 if (VecTy || IntTy)
2752 return true;
2753 if (BeginOffset > NewAllocaBeginOffset ||
2754 EndOffset < NewAllocaEndOffset)
2755 return false;
2756 auto *C = cast<ConstantInt>(II.getLength());
2757 if (C->getBitWidth() > 64)
2758 return false;
2759 const auto Len = C->getZExtValue();
2760 auto *Int8Ty = IntegerType::getInt8Ty(NewAI.getContext());
2761 auto *SrcTy = VectorType::get(Int8Ty, Len);
2762 return canConvertValue(DL, SrcTy, AllocaTy) &&
2763 DL.isLegalInteger(DL.getTypeSizeInBits(ScalarTy));
2764 }();
2765
2766 // If this doesn't map cleanly onto the alloca type, and that type isn't
2767 // a single value type, just emit a memset.
2768 if (!CanContinue) {
2769 Type *SizeTy = II.getLength()->getType();
2770 Constant *Size = ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, NewEndOffset - NewBeginOffset);
2771 CallInst *New = IRB.CreateMemSet(
2772 getNewAllocaSlicePtr(IRB, OldPtr->getType()), II.getValue(), Size,
2773 getSliceAlign(), II.isVolatile());
2774 if (AATags)
2775 New->setAAMetadata(AATags);
2776 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to: " << *New << "\n");
2777 return false;
2778 }
2779
2780 // If we can represent this as a simple value, we have to build the actual
2781 // value to store, which requires expanding the byte present in memset to
2782 // a sensible representation for the alloca type. This is essentially
2783 // splatting the byte to a sufficiently wide integer, splatting it across
2784 // any desired vector width, and bitcasting to the final type.
2785 Value *V;
2786
2787 if (VecTy) {
2788 // If this is a memset of a vectorized alloca, insert it.
2789 assert(ElementTy == ScalarTy);
2790
2791 unsigned BeginIndex = getIndex(NewBeginOffset);
2792 unsigned EndIndex = getIndex(NewEndOffset);
2793 assert(EndIndex > BeginIndex && "Empty vector!");
2794 unsigned NumElements = EndIndex - BeginIndex;
2795 assert(NumElements <= VecTy->getNumElements() && "Too many elements!");
2796
2797 Value *Splat =
2798 getIntegerSplat(II.getValue(), DL.getTypeSizeInBits(ElementTy) / 8);
2799 Splat = convertValue(DL, IRB, Splat, ElementTy);
2800 if (NumElements > 1)
2801 Splat = getVectorSplat(Splat, NumElements);
2802
2803 Value *Old = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(NewAI.getAllocatedType(), &NewAI,
2804 NewAI.getAlignment(), "oldload");
2805 V = insertVector(IRB, Old, Splat, BeginIndex, "vec");
2806 } else if (IntTy) {
2807 // If this is a memset on an alloca where we can widen stores, insert the
2808 // set integer.
2809 assert(!II.isVolatile());
2810
2811 uint64_t Size = NewEndOffset - NewBeginOffset;
2812 V = getIntegerSplat(II.getValue(), Size);
2813
2814 if (IntTy && (BeginOffset != NewAllocaBeginOffset ||
2815 EndOffset != NewAllocaBeginOffset)) {
2816 Value *Old = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(NewAI.getAllocatedType(), &NewAI,
2817 NewAI.getAlignment(), "oldload");
2818 Old = convertValue(DL, IRB, Old, IntTy);
2819 uint64_t Offset = NewBeginOffset - NewAllocaBeginOffset;
2820 V = insertInteger(DL, IRB, Old, V, Offset, "insert");
2821 } else {
2822 assert(V->getType() == IntTy &&
2823 "Wrong type for an alloca wide integer!");
2824 }
2825 V = convertValue(DL, IRB, V, AllocaTy);
2826 } else {
2827 // Established these invariants above.
2828 assert(NewBeginOffset == NewAllocaBeginOffset);
2829 assert(NewEndOffset == NewAllocaEndOffset);
2830
2831 V = getIntegerSplat(II.getValue(), DL.getTypeSizeInBits(ScalarTy) / 8);
2832 if (VectorType *AllocaVecTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(AllocaTy))
2833 V = getVectorSplat(V, AllocaVecTy->getNumElements());
2834
2835 V = convertValue(DL, IRB, V, AllocaTy);
2836 }
2837
2838 StoreInst *New = IRB.CreateAlignedStore(V, &NewAI, NewAI.getAlignment(),
2839 II.isVolatile());
2840 if (AATags)
2841 New->setAAMetadata(AATags);
2842 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to: " << *New << "\n");
2843 return !II.isVolatile();
2844 }
2845
2846 bool visitMemTransferInst(MemTransferInst &II) {
2847 // Rewriting of memory transfer instructions can be a bit tricky. We break
2848 // them into two categories: split intrinsics and unsplit intrinsics.
2849
2850 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " original: " << II << "\n");
2851
2852 AAMDNodes AATags;
2853 II.getAAMetadata(AATags);
2854
2855 bool IsDest = &II.getRawDestUse() == OldUse;
2856 assert((IsDest && II.getRawDest() == OldPtr) ||
2857 (!IsDest && II.getRawSource() == OldPtr));
2858
2859 unsigned SliceAlign = getSliceAlign();
2860
2861 // For unsplit intrinsics, we simply modify the source and destination
2862 // pointers in place. This isn't just an optimization, it is a matter of
2863 // correctness. With unsplit intrinsics we may be dealing with transfers
2864 // within a single alloca before SROA ran, or with transfers that have
2865 // a variable length. We may also be dealing with memmove instead of
2866 // memcpy, and so simply updating the pointers is the necessary for us to
2867 // update both source and dest of a single call.
2868 if (!IsSplittable) {
2869 Value *AdjustedPtr = getNewAllocaSlicePtr(IRB, OldPtr->getType());
2870 if (IsDest) {
2871 II.setDest(AdjustedPtr);
2872 II.setDestAlignment(SliceAlign);
2873 }
2874 else {
2875 II.setSource(AdjustedPtr);
2876 II.setSourceAlignment(SliceAlign);
2877 }
2878
2879 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to: " << II << "\n");
2880 deleteIfTriviallyDead(OldPtr);
2881 return false;
2882 }
2883 // For split transfer intrinsics we have an incredibly useful assurance:
2884 // the source and destination do not reside within the same alloca, and at
2885 // least one of them does not escape. This means that we can replace
2886 // memmove with memcpy, and we don't need to worry about all manner of
2887 // downsides to splitting and transforming the operations.
2888
2889 // If this doesn't map cleanly onto the alloca type, and that type isn't
2890 // a single value type, just emit a memcpy.
2891 bool EmitMemCpy =
2892 !VecTy && !IntTy &&
2893 (BeginOffset > NewAllocaBeginOffset || EndOffset < NewAllocaEndOffset ||
2894 SliceSize != DL.getTypeStoreSize(NewAI.getAllocatedType()) ||
2895 !NewAI.getAllocatedType()->isSingleValueType());
2896
2897 // If we're just going to emit a memcpy, the alloca hasn't changed, and the
2898 // size hasn't been shrunk based on analysis of the viable range, this is
2899 // a no-op.
2900 if (EmitMemCpy && &OldAI == &NewAI) {
2901 // Ensure the start lines up.
2902 assert(NewBeginOffset == BeginOffset);
2903
2904 // Rewrite the size as needed.
2905 if (NewEndOffset != EndOffset)
2906 II.setLength(ConstantInt::get(II.getLength()->getType(),
2907 NewEndOffset - NewBeginOffset));
2908 return false;
2909 }
2910 // Record this instruction for deletion.
2911 Pass.DeadInsts.insert(&II);
2912
2913 // Strip all inbounds GEPs and pointer casts to try to dig out any root
2914 // alloca that should be re-examined after rewriting this instruction.
2915 Value *OtherPtr = IsDest ? II.getRawSource() : II.getRawDest();
2916 if (AllocaInst *AI =
2917 dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(OtherPtr->stripInBoundsOffsets())) {
2918 assert(AI != &OldAI && AI != &NewAI &&
2919 "Splittable transfers cannot reach the same alloca on both ends.");
2920 Pass.Worklist.insert(AI);
2921 }
2922
2923 Type *OtherPtrTy = OtherPtr->getType();
2924 unsigned OtherAS = OtherPtrTy->getPointerAddressSpace();
2925
2926 // Compute the relative offset for the other pointer within the transfer.
2927 unsigned OffsetWidth = DL.getIndexSizeInBits(OtherAS);
2928 APInt OtherOffset(OffsetWidth, NewBeginOffset - BeginOffset);
2929 unsigned OtherAlign =
2930 IsDest ? II.getSourceAlignment() : II.getDestAlignment();
2931 OtherAlign = MinAlign(OtherAlign ? OtherAlign : 1,
2932 OtherOffset.zextOrTrunc(64).getZExtValue());
2933
2934#if 0
2935 // XXXAR: if we are using a CHERI capability we must emit a memcpy if the
2936 // other type is not aligned to the capability size.
2937 // XXXAR: This causes errors later on in StackColoring since it seems to
2938 // cause lifetime confusion. Emit an unaligned capability load/store instead
2939 // and just expanding it to memcpy() in the backend seems like the easier
2940 // solution to this problem.
2941 // See https://github.com/CTSRD-CHERI/llvm-project/issues/301
2942 if (isCheriPointer(NewAI.getAllocatedType(), &DL)) {
2943 if (OtherAlign < DL.getABITypeAlignment(NewAI.getAllocatedType())) {
2944 EmitMemCpy = true;
2945 llvm_unreachable("SROA created underaligned capability load/store and "
2946 "the workaround causes runtime crashes!");
2947 }
2948 }
2949#endif
2950
2951 if (EmitMemCpy) {
2952 // Compute the other pointer, folding as much as possible to produce
2953 // a single, simple GEP in most cases.
2954 OtherPtr = getAdjustedPtr(IRB, DL, OtherPtr, OtherOffset, OtherPtrTy,
2955 OtherPtr->getName() + ".");
2956
2957 Value *OurPtr = getNewAllocaSlicePtr(IRB, OldPtr->getType());
2958 Type *SizeTy = II.getLength()->getType();
2959 Constant *Size = ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, NewEndOffset - NewBeginOffset);
2960
2961 Value *DestPtr, *SrcPtr;
2962 unsigned DestAlign, SrcAlign;
2963 // Note: IsDest is true iff we're copying into the new alloca slice
2964 if (IsDest) {
2965 DestPtr = OurPtr;
2966 DestAlign = SliceAlign;
2967 SrcPtr = OtherPtr;
2968 SrcAlign = OtherAlign;
2969 } else {
2970 DestPtr = OtherPtr;
2971 DestAlign = OtherAlign;
2972 SrcPtr = OurPtr;
2973 SrcAlign = SliceAlign;
2974 }
2975 CallInst *New = IRB.CreateMemCpy(DestPtr, DestAlign, SrcPtr, SrcAlign,
2976 Size, II.isVolatile());
2977 if (AATags)
2978 New->setAAMetadata(AATags);
2979 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to: " << *New << "\n");
2980 return false;
2981 }
2982
2983 bool IsWholeAlloca = NewBeginOffset == NewAllocaBeginOffset &&
2984 NewEndOffset == NewAllocaEndOffset;
2985 uint64_t Size = NewEndOffset - NewBeginOffset;
2986 unsigned BeginIndex = VecTy ? getIndex(NewBeginOffset) : 0;
2987 unsigned EndIndex = VecTy ? getIndex(NewEndOffset) : 0;
2988 unsigned NumElements = EndIndex - BeginIndex;
2989 IntegerType *SubIntTy =
2990 IntTy ? Type::getIntNTy(IntTy->getContext(), Size * 8) : nullptr;
2991
2992 // Reset the other pointer type to match the register type we're going to
2993 // use, but using the address space of the original other pointer.
2994 Type *OtherTy;
2995 if (VecTy && !IsWholeAlloca) {
2996 if (NumElements == 1)
2997 OtherTy = VecTy->getElementType();
2998 else
2999 OtherTy = VectorType::get(VecTy->getElementType(), NumElements);
3000 } else if (IntTy && !IsWholeAlloca) {
3001 OtherTy = SubIntTy;
3002 } else {
3003 OtherTy = NewAllocaTy;
3004 }
3005 OtherPtrTy = OtherTy->getPointerTo(OtherAS);
3006
3007 Value *SrcPtr = getAdjustedPtr(IRB, DL, OtherPtr, OtherOffset, OtherPtrTy,
3008 OtherPtr->getName() + ".");
3009 unsigned SrcAlign = OtherAlign;
3010 Value *DstPtr = &NewAI;
3011 unsigned DstAlign = SliceAlign;
3012 if (!IsDest) {
3013 std::swap(SrcPtr, DstPtr);
3014 std::swap(SrcAlign, DstAlign);
3015 }
3016
3017 Value *Src;
3018 if (VecTy && !IsWholeAlloca && !IsDest) {
3019 Src = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(NewAI.getAllocatedType(), &NewAI,
3020 NewAI.getAlignment(), "load");
3021 Src = extractVector(IRB, Src, BeginIndex, EndIndex, "vec");
3022 } else if (IntTy && !IsWholeAlloca && !IsDest) {
3023 Src = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(NewAI.getAllocatedType(), &NewAI,
3024 NewAI.getAlignment(), "load");
3025 Src = convertValue(DL, IRB, Src, IntTy);
3026 uint64_t Offset = NewBeginOffset - NewAllocaBeginOffset;
3027 Src = extractInteger(DL, IRB, Src, SubIntTy, Offset, "extract");
3028 } else {
3029 LoadInst *Load = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(OtherTy, SrcPtr, SrcAlign,
3030 II.isVolatile(), "copyload");
3031 if (AATags)
3032 Load->setAAMetadata(AATags);
3033 Src = Load;
3034 }
3035
3036 if (VecTy && !IsWholeAlloca && IsDest) {
3037 Value *Old = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(NewAI.getAllocatedType(), &NewAI,
3038 NewAI.getAlignment(), "oldload");
3039 Src = insertVector(IRB, Old, Src, BeginIndex, "vec");
3040 } else if (IntTy && !IsWholeAlloca && IsDest) {
3041 Value *Old = IRB.CreateAlignedLoad(NewAI.getAllocatedType(), &NewAI,
3042 NewAI.getAlignment(), "oldload");
3043 Old = convertValue(DL, IRB, Old, IntTy);
3044 uint64_t Offset = NewBeginOffset - NewAllocaBeginOffset;
3045 Src = insertInteger(DL, IRB, Old, Src, Offset, "insert");
3046 Src = convertValue(DL, IRB, Src, NewAllocaTy);
3047 }
3048
3049 StoreInst *Store = cast<StoreInst>(
3050 IRB.CreateAlignedStore(Src, DstPtr, DstAlign, II.isVolatile()));
3051 if (AATags)
3052 Store->setAAMetadata(AATags);
3053 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to: " << *Store << "\n");
3054 return !II.isVolatile();
3055 }
3056
3057 bool visitIntrinsicInst(IntrinsicInst &II) {
3058 assert(II.isLifetimeStartOrEnd());
3059 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " original: " << II << "\n");
3060 assert(II.getArgOperand(1) == OldPtr);
3061
3062 // Record this instruction for deletion.
3063 Pass.DeadInsts.insert(&II);
3064
3065 // Lifetime intrinsics are only promotable if they cover the whole alloca.
3066 // Therefore, we drop lifetime intrinsics which don't cover the whole
3067 // alloca.
3068 // (In theory, intrinsics which partially cover an alloca could be
3069 // promoted, but PromoteMemToReg doesn't handle that case.)
3070 // FIXME: Check whether the alloca is promotable before dropping the
3071 // lifetime intrinsics?
3072 if (NewBeginOffset != NewAllocaBeginOffset ||
3073 NewEndOffset != NewAllocaEndOffset)
3074 return true;
3075
3076 ConstantInt *Size =
3077 ConstantInt::get(cast<IntegerType>(II.getArgOperand(0)->getType()),
3078 NewEndOffset - NewBeginOffset);
3079 // Lifetime intrinsics always expect an i8* so directly get such a pointer
3080 // for the new alloca slice.
3081 Type *PointerTy = IRB.getInt8PtrTy(OldPtr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace());
3082 Value *Ptr = getNewAllocaSlicePtr(IRB, PointerTy);
3083 Value *New;
3084 if (II.getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::lifetime_start)
3085 New = IRB.CreateLifetimeStart(Ptr, Size);
3086 else
3087 New = IRB.CreateLifetimeEnd(Ptr, Size);
3088
3089 (void)New;
3090 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to: " << *New << "\n");
3091
3092 return true;
3093 }
3094
3095 void fixLoadStoreAlign(Instruction &Root) {
3096 // This algorithm implements the same visitor loop as
3097 // hasUnsafePHIOrSelectUse, and fixes the alignment of each load
3098 // or store found.
3099 SmallPtrSet<Instruction *, 4> Visited;
3100 SmallVector<Instruction *, 4> Uses;
3101 Visited.insert(&Root);
3102 Uses.push_back(&Root);
3103 do {
3104 Instruction *I = Uses.pop_back_val();
3105
3106 if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(I)) {
3107 unsigned LoadAlign = LI->getAlignment();
3108 if (!LoadAlign)
3109 LoadAlign = DL.getABITypeAlignment(LI->getType());
3110 LI->setAlignment(std::min(LoadAlign, getSliceAlign()));
3111 continue;
3112 }
3113 if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(I)) {
3114 unsigned StoreAlign = SI->getAlignment();
3115 if (!StoreAlign) {
3116 Value *Op = SI->getOperand(0);
3117 StoreAlign = DL.getABITypeAlignment(Op->getType());
3118 }
3119 SI->setAlignment(std::min(StoreAlign, getSliceAlign()));
3120 continue;
3121 }
3122
3123 assert(isa<BitCastInst>(I) || isa<PHINode>(I) ||
3124 isa<SelectInst>(I) || isa<GetElementPtrInst>(I));
3125 for (User *U : I->users())
3126 if (Visited.insert(cast<Instruction>(U)).second)
3127 Uses.push_back(cast<Instruction>(U));
3128 } while (!Uses.empty());
3129 }
3130
3131 bool visitPHINode(PHINode &PN) {
3132 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " original: " << PN << "\n");
3133 assert(BeginOffset >= NewAllocaBeginOffset && "PHIs are unsplittable");
3134 assert(EndOffset <= NewAllocaEndOffset && "PHIs are unsplittable");
3135
3136 // We would like to compute a new pointer in only one place, but have it be
3137 // as local as possible to the PHI. To do that, we re-use the location of
3138 // the old pointer, which necessarily must be in the right position to
3139 // dominate the PHI.
3140 IRBuilderTy PtrBuilder(IRB);
3141 if (isa<PHINode>(OldPtr))
3142 PtrBuilder.SetInsertPoint(&*OldPtr->getParent()->getFirstInsertionPt());
3143 else
3144 PtrBuilder.SetInsertPoint(OldPtr);
3145 PtrBuilder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(OldPtr->getDebugLoc());
3146
3147 Value *NewPtr = getNewAllocaSlicePtr(PtrBuilder, OldPtr->getType());
3148 // Replace the operands which were using the old pointer.
3149 std::replace(PN.op_begin(), PN.op_end(), cast<Value>(OldPtr), NewPtr);
3150
3151 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to: " << PN << "\n");
3152 deleteIfTriviallyDead(OldPtr);
3153
3154 // Fix the alignment of any loads or stores using this PHI node.
3155 fixLoadStoreAlign(PN);
3156
3157 // PHIs can't be promoted on their own, but often can be speculated. We
3158 // check the speculation outside of the rewriter so that we see the
3159 // fully-rewritten alloca.
3160 PHIUsers.insert(&PN);
3161 return true;
3162 }
3163
3164 bool visitSelectInst(SelectInst &SI) {
3165 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " original: " << SI << "\n");
3166 assert((SI.getTrueValue() == OldPtr || SI.getFalseValue() == OldPtr) &&
3167 "Pointer isn't an operand!");
3168 assert(BeginOffset >= NewAllocaBeginOffset && "Selects are unsplittable");
3169 assert(EndOffset <= NewAllocaEndOffset && "Selects are unsplittable");
3170
3171 Value *NewPtr = getNewAllocaSlicePtr(IRB, OldPtr->getType());
3172 // Replace the operands which were using the old pointer.
3173 if (SI.getOperand(1) == OldPtr)
3174 SI.setOperand(1, NewPtr);
3175 if (SI.getOperand(2) == OldPtr)
3176 SI.setOperand(2, NewPtr);
3177
3178 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to: " << SI << "\n");
3179 deleteIfTriviallyDead(OldPtr);
3180
3181 // Fix the alignment of any loads or stores using this select.
3182 fixLoadStoreAlign(SI);
3183
3184 // Selects can't be promoted on their own, but often can be speculated. We
3185 // check the speculation outside of the rewriter so that we see the
3186 // fully-rewritten alloca.
3187 SelectUsers.insert(&SI);
3188 return true;
3189 }

3194/// Visitor to rewrite aggregate loads and stores as scalar.
3195///
3196/// This pass aggressively rewrites all aggregate loads and stores on
3197/// a particular pointer (or any pointer derived from it which we can identify)
3198/// with scalar loads and stores.
3199class AggLoadStoreRewriter : public InstVisitor<AggLoadStoreRewriter, bool> {
3200 // Befriend the base class so it can delegate to private visit methods.
3201 friend class InstVisitor<AggLoadStoreRewriter, bool>;
3202
3203 /// Queue of pointer uses to analyze and potentially rewrite.
3204 SmallVector<Use *, 8> Queue;
3205
3206 /// Set to prevent us from cycling with phi nodes and loops.
3207 SmallPtrSet<User *, 8> Visited;
3208
3209 /// The current pointer use being rewritten. This is used to dig up the used
3210 /// value (as opposed to the user).
3211 Use *U;
3212
3213 /// Used to calculate offsets, and hence alignment, of subobjects.
3214 const DataLayout &DL;
3215
3216public:
3217 AggLoadStoreRewriter(const DataLayout &DL) : DL(DL) {}
3218
3219 /// Rewrite loads and stores through a pointer and all pointers derived from
3220 /// it.
3221 bool rewrite(Instruction &I) {
3222 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Rewriting FCA loads and stores...\n");
3223 enqueueUsers(I);
3224 bool Changed = false;
3225 while (!Queue.empty()) {
3226 U = Queue.pop_back_val();
3227 Changed |= visit(cast<Instruction>(U->getUser()));
3228 }
3229 return Changed;
3230 }
3231
3232private:
3233 /// Enqueue all the users of the given instruction for further processing.
3234 /// This uses a set to de-duplicate users.
3235 void enqueueUsers(Instruction &I) {
3236 for (Use &U : I.uses())
3237 if (Visited.insert(U.getUser()).second)
3238 Queue.push_back(&U);
3239 }
3240
3241 // Conservative default is to not rewrite anything.
3242 bool visitInstruction(Instruction &I) { return false; }

3244 /// Generic recursive split emission class.
3245 template <typename Derived> class OpSplitter {
3246 protected:
3247 /// The builder used to form new instructions.
3248 IRBuilderTy IRB;
3249
3250 /// The indices which to be used with insert- or extractvalue to select the
3251 /// appropriate value within the aggregate.
3252 SmallVector<unsigned, 4> Indices;
3253
3254 /// The indices to a GEP instruction which will move Ptr to the correct slot
3255 /// within the aggregate.
3256 SmallVector<Value *, 4> GEPIndices;
3257
3258 /// The base pointer of the original op, used as a base for GEPing the
3259 /// split operations.
3260 Value *Ptr;
3261
3262 /// The base pointee type being GEPed into.
3263 Type *BaseTy;
3264
3265 /// Known alignment of the base pointer.
3266 unsigned BaseAlign;
3267
3268 /// To calculate offset of each component so we can correctly deduce
3269 /// alignments.
3270 const DataLayout &DL;
3271
3272 /// Initialize the splitter with an insertion point, Ptr and start with a
3273 /// single zero GEP index.
3274 OpSplitter(Instruction *InsertionPoint, Value *Ptr, Type *BaseTy,
3275 unsigned BaseAlign, const DataLayout &DL)
3276 : IRB(InsertionPoint), GEPIndices(1, IRB.getInt32(0)), Ptr(Ptr),
3277 BaseTy(BaseTy), BaseAlign(BaseAlign), DL(DL) {}
3278
3279 public:
3280 /// Generic recursive split emission routine.
3281 ///
3282 /// This method recursively splits an aggregate op (load or store) into
3283 /// scalar or vector ops. It splits recursively until it hits a single value
3284 /// and emits that single value operation via the template argument.
3285 ///
3286 /// The logic of this routine relies on GEPs and insertvalue and
3287 /// extractvalue all operating with the same fundamental index list, merely
3288 /// formatted differently (GEPs need actual values).
3289 ///
3290 /// \param Ty The type being split recursively into smaller ops.
3291 /// \param Agg The aggregate value being built up or stored, depending on
3292 /// whether this is splitting a load or a store respectively.
3293 void emitSplitOps(Type *Ty, Value *&Agg, const Twine &Name) {
3294 if (Ty->isSingleValueType()) {
3295 unsigned Offset = DL.getIndexedOffsetInType(BaseTy, GEPIndices);
3296 return static_cast<Derived *>(this)->emitFunc(
3297 Ty, Agg, MinAlign(BaseAlign, Offset), Name);
3298 }
3299
3300 if (ArrayType *ATy = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(Ty)) {
3301 unsigned OldSize = Indices.size();
3302 (void)OldSize;
3303 for (unsigned Idx = 0, Size = ATy->getNumElements(); Idx != Size;
3304 ++Idx) {
3305 assert(Indices.size() == OldSize && "Did not return to the old size");
3306 Indices.push_back(Idx);
3307 GEPIndices.push_back(IRB.getInt32(Idx));
3308 emitSplitOps(ATy->getElementType(), Agg, Name + "." + Twine(Idx));
3309 GEPIndices.pop_back();
3310 Indices.pop_back();
3311 }
3312 return;
3313 }
3314
3315 if (StructType *STy = dyn_cast<StructType>(Ty)) {
3316 unsigned OldSize = Indices.size();
3317 (void)OldSize;
3318 for (unsigned Idx = 0, Size = STy->getNumElements(); Idx != Size;
3319 ++Idx) {
3320 assert(Indices.size() == OldSize && "Did not return to the old size");
3321 Indices.push_back(Idx);
3322 GEPIndices.push_back(IRB.getInt32(Idx));
3323 emitSplitOps(STy->getElementType(Idx), Agg, Name + "." + Twine(Idx));
3324 GEPIndices.pop_back();
3325 Indices.pop_back();
3326 }
3327 return;
3328 }
3329
3330 llvm_unreachable("Only arrays and structs are aggregate loadable types");
3331 }
3332 };

3334 struct LoadOpSplitter : public OpSplitter<LoadOpSplitter> {
3335 AAMDNodes AATags;
3336
3337 LoadOpSplitter(Instruction *InsertionPoint, Value *Ptr, Type *BaseTy,
3338 AAMDNodes AATags, unsigned BaseAlign, const DataLayout &DL)
3339 : OpSplitter<LoadOpSplitter>(InsertionPoint, Ptr, BaseTy, BaseAlign,

3342 /// Emit a leaf load of a single value. This is called at the leaves of the
3343 /// recursive emission to actually load values.

3345 assert(Ty->isSingleValueType());

3347 Value *GEP =
3348 IRB.CreateInBoundsGEP(BaseTy, Ptr, GEPIndices, Name + ".gep");
